http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Krishna-Yadav-quits-as-TDP-vice-president/article14014719.ece

Miffed with the selection process of the candidates for the upcoming GHMC elections, former Telugu Desam Party (TDP) Minister and senior leader C. Krishna Yadav resigned from the post of vice-president of Telangana TDP. On Friday, Mr. Yadav alleged that party tickets have been sold to undeserving candidates leaving out sitting corporators and loyal party workers.“Fifteen sitting TDP corporators representing wards like Nagole, Moosarambagh, Himayatnagar and Aliyabad have been denied tickets,” said Mr. Yadav,